  "summary": "Hello, i joined a friends aternos and then i changed my minecraft name, it restarted my game",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "i joined a friends aternos and then i changed my minecraft name, i joined it later on and got restarted, items and all. i got respawned at the world spawn point and had to try and get my loot back but failed. i don t know what to do? n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Launch Minecraft and log into your account.\n2. Join your friend's Aternos server.\n3. Once you are in the game, open the Minecraft settings menu.\n4. Navigate to the \"Profile\" section and change your Minecraft username.\n5. Confirm the username change and exit back to the game.\n6. Observe that the game restarts automatically after the username change.\n7. After the game restarts, rejoin your friend's Aternos server.\n8. Note that upon rejoining, your character is respawned at the world spawn point and all previously held items are lost.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "When joining a friend's Aternos server, the player changed their Minecraft username. Upon attempting to reconnect to the server after the name change, the game restarted unexpectedly. This restart resulted in the loss of all items previously held by the player, as they were respawned at the world spawn point. Consequently, the player was unable to retrieve their lost items, leading to frustration and confusion regarding how to proceed. \n\nKey details:\n- The issue occurs specifically after changing the player's Minecraft username while connected to an Aternos server.\n- The game restart leads to a complete reset of the player's inventory, causing the loss of all items.\n- The player is respawned at the default spawn point of the world, rather than their last death location or any saved spawn point.\n- No error messages were displayed during this process, making it unclear why the restart happened or how to prevent it in the future. \n\nThis behavior significantly impacts gameplay, especially in survival scenarios where inventory management and item retention are crucial.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When a player changes their Minecraft username while connected to a friend's Aternos server, the game should not restart, and the player should remain in the world without losing any items or being respawned at the world spawn point. Instead, the player should retain their inventory and any progress made in the game. The expected behavior is that the server recognizes the new username as part of the same player session, allowing for a seamless transition without data loss. This functionality aligns with Minecraft's design of maintaining player data and inventory across username changes, ensuring players can continue their adventures without interruption.",
